author: Unreal Engine
description:
This talk recorded at Unreal Fest Stockholm will equip you with the skills to leverage Unreal Engine’s TraceLog library effectively for everyday performance profiling. 

Watch to learn how to make the most of UE’s built-in tracing tools, from using existing telemetry channels to creating your own custom trace events—along with key considerations to keep in mind.

We provide a quick overview for those unfamiliar with UE's tracing at the start before moving on to the performance and memory impact of different configurations for tracing; when to use different types of telemetry; and beyond.

Learn more about Unreal Engine here: unrealengine.com

#GameDevelopment, #DebuggingGames, #TraceLog, #Telemetry, #UnrealEngine, #UE5, #UnrealFestStockholm
title: Unpacking High-Performance Telemetry with TraceLog | Unreal Fest Stockholm 2025

author: Unreal Engine
description:
In this session recorded at Unreal Fest Stockholm, Epic’s Cody Albert provides a deep dive into the current features of SlateIM and offers some examples of how you can use it to accelerate your debug tool development.

Introduced in Unreal Engine 5.6, the SlateIM plugin leverages the existing Slate UI framework to allow for quick debug tool development and iteration in a style that tools programmers should find much more familiar than traditional Slate syntax. 

This talk covers everything from SlateIM features and usage to best practices and the SlateIM roadmap.

Learn more about Unreal Engine here: unrealengine.com

#SlateIM, #DebugTools, #UE5.6, #UnrealEngine, #UE5, #UnrealFestStockholm
title: Creating Debug Tools with SlateIM | Unreal Fest Stockholm 2025

author: Unreal Engine
description:
In this session recorded at Unreal Fest Stockholm, the Quixel team at Epic dive into the latest updates to Nanite Foliage content!

We explore new asset concepts regarding instancing; how to lean into fully opaque geometry solutions for foliage; and what the next steps are regarding animation for foliage.

There’s also a look at some of the latest content examples and how they work within our own pipeline, as well as tips on best practices.

We provide an introduction to how Unreal Engine can leverage voxels to represent foliage in the near and far distance, what you need to know to set this up, and the performance benefits it brings. 

Learn more about Unreal Engine here: unrealengine.com

#NaniteFoliage, #Quixel, #UnrealEngine, #UE5, #UnrealFestStockholm
title: The Future of Nanite Foliage | Unreal Fest Stockholm 2025
